---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Section from "../../components/ui/Section.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About | shanmuganand.m"
  description="My background, skills, and approach to software engineering."
>
  <main class="main-content page-transition">
    <!-- Inline Nav -->
    <div class="nav-links inline-nav">
      <a href="/" class="cmd-link">[ ← cd ~ ]</a>
    </div>

    <Section id="about-full" title="about">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I'm <strong>M.S.Anand</strong>, Senior Frontend Engineer based in
          Indianapolis. I build things that work — AI-powered features, API
          integrations, design systems, WebRTC platforms — and I'm currently
          learning to do a handstand, which honestly has a lot in common with
          frontend engineering. Looks simple from the outside. Deeply humbling
          once you actually try it.
        </p>

        <p>
          Six years in, I've shipped across the full frontend spectrum — from
          pixel-perfect component libraries to real-time video platforms to
          compliance tooling with complex validation engines. I don't specialize
          in one thing. I specialize in making the whole thing work, fast, and
          not fall apart at 3am.
        </p>
        <p>
          I still think most teams are overcomplicating their stack. You
          probably don't need that abstraction. What you need is a clear
          architecture, a fast feedback loop, and someone who gives a damn about
          the details from the API contract all the way down to the CSS variable
          name. That's the part I'm good at.
        </p>

        <h3>Focus Areas</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Feature Engineering:</strong> From AI-powered suggestion engines
            to real-time WebRTC platforms — I've shipped complex, stateful frontend
            features that talk to APIs, handle edge cases, and actually work in production.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Design Systems:</strong> Not the kind that lives in a Figma file
            nobody opens. The kind with typed component contracts, documented APIs,
            and enough flexibility that a junior engineer can use it without breaking
            everything.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Performance:</strong> Core Web Vitals aren't a checkbox. I've
            migrated CRA to Vite, cut build times by 80%, and obsessed over the critical
            rendering path long enough to know exactly where most teams are leaving
            time on the table.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Developer Experience:</strong> If your CI pipeline takes 20 minutes,
            your local setup needs a README, and your linting config is held together
            with hope — I've fixed those too. Fast feedback loops aren't optional,
            they're how good software gets built.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Outside the terminal</h3>
        <p>
          Currently training for my first triathlon. Also attempting a
          freestanding handstand, which is going about as well as most
          JavaScript rewrites — promising progress, unexpected setbacks, but
          committed to the outcome.
        </p>

        <h3>Hot take</h3>
        <p>
          AI won't replace good engineers. It'll replace the ones who stopped
          being curious.
        </p>

        <h3>Work Authorization</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>U.S. Permanent Resident (Green Card holder).</strong> No sponsorship
          needed. Open to remote — Indianapolis is great but the world is bigger.
        </p>
        <h3>Languages</h3>
        <p>English (Fluent), Tamil (Native)</p>
        <a href="/resume.pdf" class="btn btn-blue" target="_blank"
          >[ download resume ]</a
        >
      </div>
    </Section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .main-content {
    flex: 1;
    padding-top: 8rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .inline-nav {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cmd-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .cmd-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-blue);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .page-transition {
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s ease-out;
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(10px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  /* Typography overrides for prose */
  .prose {
    max-width: 720px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .prose li {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .prose li::before {
    content: "- ";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-blue);
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
